  "prompt": "Why did Quora limit question details to 300 words?",
  "response": "Quora's decision to limit question details to 300 words likely stems from several considerations aimed at improving user experience and content quality. Here are a few potential reasons:\n\n1. **Clarity and Focus**: Limiting the word count encourages users to articulate their questions more clearly and concisely. This can help avoid overly complex or convoluted questions that might confuse potential responders.\n\n2. **Engagement**: Shorter questions may lead to faster engagement from the community. Users are more likely to read and respond to questions that are straightforward and easy to understand.\n\n3. **Quality Control**: A word limit can help maintain the quality of the questions that are posed. It encourages users to think critically about what they are asking and ensures that only relevant details are included.\n\n4. **Improved Answers**: Concise questions allow for more focused and relevant answers. When questions are too lengthy, it can lead to confusion about what is being asked, resulting in less helpful responses.\n\n5. **User Experience**: By implementing a word limit, Quora can enhance the overall user experience by creating a more streamlined and efficient platform for asking and answering questions.\n\nThese changes reflect a broader trend in online platforms to promote clarity and engagement within their communities.",
